02rkAweH9ojfeJIlYAvgobWZTwz65KWQma1spjKiFuomsLXXW2L+GbUgh0EiKoAB0aJ{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01FYMDDQfz7urmvkguEoF3bC\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"title:\\tImplement core data structures and in-memory store with thread-safe access\\nstate:\\tOPEN\\nauthor:\\txlight05\\nlabels:\\t\\ncomments:\\t0\\nassignees:\\t\\nprojects:\\t\\nmilestone:\\t\\nnumber:\\t1\\n--\\n## Architecture Context\\nThis is the sole backend service in the system. It is called directly by the leave-portal for all data operations. It stores all state in-memory (maps with mutexes) and seeds initial employee, manager, and balance data at startup. Nothing depends on an external service — it is the system's source of truth.\\n\\n## Component Constraints\\n- **Name:** leave-service\\n- **Type:** service\\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\\n- **App Path:** `/{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"task_started\",\"task_id\":\"b6ecz9dgp\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_018txw8NvtfpL1MoJYxjUahU\",\"de{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01DehGfncGfEU1ediotqiLbM\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"title:\\tImplement POST /api/v1/leave-requests endpoint with validation\\nstate:\\tOPEN\\nauthor:\\txlight{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"r{\"type\":\"system\",\"subtype\":\"task_started\",\"task_id\":\"bz887nmh3\",\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01671jk2mQuQf7bornbMdCji\",\"description\":\"View GitHub issue #7\",\"task_type\"{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01Bd53zdGhujbMdb2D34kujL\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_019TfMAfEbFDzRVbDSEnLqMs\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"title:\\tImplement HTTP server setup and routing with structured logging\\nstate:\\tOPEN\\nauthor:\\txlight05\\nlabels:\\t\\ncomments:\\t0\\nassignees:\\t\\nprojects:\\t\\nmilestone:\\t\\nnumber:\\t9\\n--\\n## Architecture Context\\nThis is the sole backend service in the system. It is called directly by the leave-portal for all data operations. It stores all state in-memory (maps with mutexes) and seeds initial employee, manager, and balance data at startup. Nothing depends on an external service — it is the system's source of truth.\\n\\n## Component Constraints\\n- **Name:** leave-service\\n- **Type:** service\\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\\n- **App Path:** `/leave-service`\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n- Configure net/http server on port 9090\\n- Register all endpoint handlers with correct routes and HTTP methods\\n- Add request/response logging middleware\\n- Implement JSON marshaling utilities and error response helpers\\n\\n## Key Considerations\\n- Use http.MethodPost, http.MethodGet, etc. to enforce correct HTTP methods on routes\\n- Log all requests with timestamp, method, path, and response status for observability\\n- Return consistent JSON error responses with meaningful messages and correct status codes\\n\\n## Project Structure Requirements\\nCreate a production-ready project structure in the current directory:\\n- go.mod with proper module path\\n- cmd/ or main.go entry point\\n- Dockerfile (multi-stage build)\\n- Internal packages as needed (handlers/, services/, models/)\\n\\nCreate a `workload.yaml` at the root of your component directory:\\n\\n```yaml\\napiVersion: openchoreo.dev/v1alpha1\\nmetadata:\\n  name: <component-k8s-name>\\nspec:\\n  autoBuild: true\\n  autoDeploy: true\\n  endpoints:\\n    - name: http\\n      port: <port-your-app-listens-on>\\n      type: HTTP\\n      basePath: /\\n      visibility:\\n        - external\\n```\\n\\nThe port must match the port your application listens on. Adjust endpoint type, basePath, and add dependencies as needed.\\n\\nThe platform will handle git commit, push, build, and deploy automatically.\\n## OpenAPI Spec\\n\\n```yaml\\nopenapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave Management API\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Backend API for WSO2 internal leave management system\\nservers:\\n  - url: http://localhost:9090\\n    description: Development server\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check endpoint\\n      operationId: healthCheck\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Service is healthy\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\\n  /api/v1/leave-requests:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Submit a new leave request\\n      operationId: createLeaveRequest\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required:\\n                - employeeId\\n                - leaveType\\n                - startDate\\n                - endDate\\n              properties:\\n                employeeId:\\n                  type: string\\n                leaveType:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [annual, sick, personal, unpaid]\\n                startDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                endDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                reason:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Leave request created\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request (overlapping dates, insufficient balance)\\n        '500':\\n          description: Server error\\n    get:\\n      summary: List leave requests\\n      operationId: listLeaveRequests\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employeeId\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n        - name: managerId\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n        - name: status\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n            enum: [pending, approved, denied]\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of leave requests\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n  /api/v1/leave-requests/{id}:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get a specific leave request\\n      operationId: getLeaveRequest\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave request details\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '404':\\n          description: Leave request not found\\n    patch:\\n      summary: Update leave request status (approve/deny)\\n      operationId: updateLeaveRequestStatus\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required:\\n                - status\\n                - reviewerId\\n              properties:\\n                status:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [approved, denied]\\n                reviewerId:\\n                  type: string\\n                comments:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave request updated\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '403':\\n          description: Unauthorized (not the manager)\\n        '404':\\n          description: Leave request not found\\n  /api/v1/employees/{id}/balance:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get employee leave balance\\n      operationId: getLeaveBalance\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave balance by type\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  employeeId:\\n                    type: string\\n                  balances:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: object\\n                      properties:\\n                        leaveType:\\n                          type: string\\n                        allocated:\\n                          type: number\\n                        used:\\n                          type: number\\n                        remaining:\\n                          type: number\\n        '404':\\n          description: Employee not found\\n    put:\\n      summary: Set employee annual leave allocation (HR admin only)\\n      operationId: setLeaveAllocation\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required:\\n                - leaveType\\n                - allocated\\n              properties:\\n                leaveType:\\n                  type: string\\n                allocated:\\n                  type: number\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Allocation updated\\n        '403':\\n          description: Unauthorized (not HR admin)\\ncomponents:\\n  schemas:\\n    LeaveRequest:\\n      type: object\\n      properties:\\n        id:\\n          type: string\\n        employeeId:\\n          type: string\\n        leaveType:\\n          type: string\\n        startDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        endDate:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date\\n        reason:\\n          type: string\\n        status:\\n          type: string\\n          enum: [pending, approved, denied]\\n        reviewerId:\\n          type: string\\n        reviewerComments:\\n          type: string\\n        createdAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\\n        updatedAt:\\n          type: string\\n          format: date-time\\n```\\n\\n## Agent Instructions\\nSet up the main HTTP server using net/http listening on port 9090. Register all implemented handlers to their respective routes. Add JSON encoding/decoding utilities. Implement structured logging to stdout for all incoming requests (method, path, status code) and errors. Add middleware for CORS if needed. Ensure graceful startup and log server readiness.\\n\\n## Working Directory\\nYou are working inside a cloned git repository at your component's source directory.\\nCreate all files relative to this directory. Do NOT create files outside it.\\n\\n## General Constraints\\n- Write ALL files in the current working directory (do NOT create files outside it).\\n- The component must have a Dockerfile for containerized builds.\\n- Implement the full API contract from the task — every endpoint must be functional.\\n- Use the dependencies listed to understand what other services this component talks to.\\n- The app MUST start without any required environment variables — use sensible hardcoded defaults for all config (JWT secrets, DB paths, API URLs, etc.). Environment variables may override defaults but must never be required.\\n- Do NOT stub or mock — write real, working implementations.\\n- Do NOT run, start, or execute the application server locally. Only write source files. The platform builds and deploys your code automatically — local execution is unnecessary and will cause port conflicts.\\n- If you must run a quick compile check (e.g. `go build`, `tsc --noEmit`), do so without starting a server. Never use `go run`, `npm start`, `node server.js`, or any command that starts a long-running process.\",\"is_error\":false}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"4f4371ae-b5cb-4282-90f7-3ba15cbb2514\",\"uuid\":\"3ed964c1-f5b7-45f9-9abe-bbb08877fe91\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-23T13:10:13.825Z\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"stdout\":\"title:\\tImplement HTTP server setup and routing with structured logging\\nstate:\\tOPEN\\nauthor:\\txlight05\\nlabels:\\t\\ncomments:\\t0\\nassignees:\\t\\nprojects:\\t\\nmilestone:\\t\\nnumber:\\t9\\n--\\n## Architecture Context\\nThis is the sole backend service in the system. It is called directly by the leave-portal for all data operations. It stores all state in-memory (maps with mutexes) and seeds initial employee, manager, and balance data at startup. Nothing depends on an external service — it is the system's source of truth.\\n\\n## Component Constraints\\n- **Name:** leave-service\\n- **Type:** service\\n- **Language/Stack:** Go\\n- **App Path:** `/leave-service`\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n- Configure net/http server on port 9090\\n- Register all endpoint handlers with correct routes and HTTP methods\\n- Add request/response logging middleware\\n- Implement JSON marshaling utilities and error response helpers\\n\\n## Key Considerations\\n- Use http.MethodPost, http.MethodGet, etc. to enforce correct HTTP methods on routes\\n- Log all requests with timestamp, method, path, and response status for observability\\n- Return consistent JSON error responses with meaningful messages and correct status codes\\n\\n## Project Structure Requirements\\nCreate a production-ready project structure in the current directory:\\n- go.mod with proper module path\\n- cmd/ or main.go entry point\\n- Dockerfile (multi-stage build)\\n- Internal packages as needed (handlers/, services/, models/)\\n\\nCreate a `workload.yaml` at the root of your component directory:\\n\\n```yaml\\napiVersion: openchoreo.dev/v1alpha1\\nmetadata:\\n  name: <component-k8s-name>\\nspec:\\n  autoBuild: true\\n  autoDeploy: true\\n  endpoints:\\n    - name: http\\n      port: <port-your-app-listens-on>\\n      type: HTTP\\n      basePath: /\\n      visibility:\\n        - external\\n```\\n\\nThe port must match the port your application listens on. Adjust endpoint type, basePath, and add dependencies as needed.\\n\\nThe platform will handle git commit, push, build, and deploy automatically.\\n## OpenAPI Spec\\n\\n```yaml\\nopenapi: 3.0.3\\ninfo:\\n  title: Leave Management API\\n  version: 1.0.0\\n  description: Backend API for WSO2 internal leave management system\\nservers:\\n  - url: http://localhost:9090\\n    description: Development server\\npaths:\\n  /health:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Health check endpoint\\n      operationId: healthCheck\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Service is healthy\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  status:\\n                    type: string\\n                    example: ok\\n  /api/v1/leave-requests:\\n    post:\\n      summary: Submit a new leave request\\n      operationId: createLeaveRequest\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required:\\n                - employeeId\\n                - leaveType\\n                - startDate\\n                - endDate\\n              properties:\\n                employeeId:\\n                  type: string\\n                leaveType:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [annual, sick, personal, unpaid]\\n                startDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                endDate:\\n                  type: string\\n                  format: date\\n                reason:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '201':\\n          description: Leave request created\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '400':\\n          description: Invalid request (overlapping dates, insufficient balance)\\n        '500':\\n          description: Server error\\n    get:\\n      summary: List leave requests\\n      operationId: listLeaveRequests\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: employeeId\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n        - name: managerId\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n        - name: status\\n          in: query\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n            enum: [pending, approved, denied]\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: List of leave requests\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: array\\n                items:\\n                  $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n  /api/v1/leave-requests/{id}:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get a specific leave request\\n      operationId: getLeaveRequest\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave request details\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '404':\\n          description: Leave request not found\\n    patch:\\n      summary: Update leave request status (approve/deny)\\n      operationId: updateLeaveRequestStatus\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      requestBody:\\n        required: true\\n        content:\\n          application/json:\\n            schema:\\n              type: object\\n              required:\\n                - status\\n                - reviewerId\\n              properties:\\n                status:\\n                  type: string\\n                  enum: [approved, denied]\\n                reviewerId:\\n                  type: string\\n                comments:\\n                  type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave request updated\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                $ref: '#/components/schemas/LeaveRequest'\\n        '403':\\n          description: Unauthorized (not the manager)\\n        '404':\\n          description: Leave request not found\\n  /api/v1/employees/{id}/balance:\\n    get:\\n      summary: Get employee leave balance\\n      operationId: getLeaveBalance\\n      parameters:\\n        - name: id\\n          in: path\\n          required: true\\n          schema:\\n            type: string\\n      responses:\\n        '200':\\n          description: Leave balance by type\\n          content:\\n            application/json:\\n              schema:\\n                type: object\\n                properties:\\n                  employeeId:\\n                    type: string\\n                  balances:\\n                    type: array\\n                    items:\\n                      type: object\\n                      properties:\\n                        leaveType:\\n                          type: string\\n                        allocated:\\n                          type: number\\n                        u