{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XzeHQxWDMGaZVEs8V45jGB","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport type { TaskInfo } from \"./types.js\";\n2\t\n3\tconst tasks = new Map<string, TaskInfo>();\n4\t\n5\texport function get(taskId: string): TaskInfo | undefined {\n6\t  return tasks.get(taskId);\n7\t}\n8\t\n9\texport function set(taskId: string, info: TaskInfo): void {\n10\t  tasks.set(taskId, info);\n11\t}\n12\t\n13\texport function markDone(taskId: string, exitCode: number, error?: string): void {\n14\t  const info = tasks.get(taskId);\n15\t  if (!info) return;\n16\t  info.done = true;\n17\t  info.exitCode = exitCode;\n18\t  if (error) info.error = error;\n19\t  info.query = undefined;\n20\t}\n21\t\n22\texport function runningCount(): number {\n23\t  let n = 0;\n24\t  for (const info of tasks.values()) if (!info.done) n++;\n25\t  return n;\n26\t}\n27\t\n28\texport function allTasks(): TaskInfo[] {\n29\t  return [...tasks.values()];\n30\t}\n31\t\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01SumBnGJdMrxaa1bwmn9L2p","session_id":"4f4371ae-b5cb-4282-90f7-3ba15cbb2514","uuid":"6ddf4cbb-0002-486e-92a1-8553ba951f63","timestamp":"2026-04-23T13:31:00.150Z"}
