{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NaxqjxWMqd5UCPPSBbfp84","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Docker image is being built — it's pulling `golang:1.23-alpine`. I'll check back in ~4.5 minutes once the download completes. Here's a summary of what's been implemented so far:\n\n---\n\n## What's been built\n\n**`GET /api/v1/employees/{id}/balance`** (the primary issue endpoint) plus the full leave-service:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `main.go` | Entry point, port 9090, CORS+Logging middleware chain |\n| `go.mod` | Module `github.com/asdlc-repos/mxcz308/leave-service`, go 1.23 |\n| `Dockerfile` | Multi-stage: `golang:1.23-alpine` builder → `scratch` final image |\n| `workload.yaml` | OpenChoreo manifest, port 9090, HTTP, external visibility |\n| `internal/models/models.go` | `LeaveRequest`, `LeaveBalance`, `EmployeeBalance`, `BalanceEntry` types |\n| `internal/store/store.go` | In-memory store with `sync.RWMutex`; seeded with emp1/emp2/emp3 (20 annual, 10 sick, 5 personal days) and mgr1→emp1/emp2 |\n| `internal/handlers/handlers.go` | All 6 endpoints from the OpenAPI spec |\n| `internal/middleware/middleware.go` | CORS + structured logging middleware |\n\n**Balance endpoint specifics:**\n- Uses `RLock` (read-only operation)\n- Returns all 4 leave types even if allocation is 0 (annual, sick, personal, unpaid)\n- 404 if employee ID doesn't exist\n- `remaining = allocated - used`"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":211,"cache_read_input_tokens":63617,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":211,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ef111ef-7270-4739-8292-7d48660af614","uuid":"2c7e8938-e0b7-47d1-bf32-51f637cd5438"}
