{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019zsaWdrscEuFctqi9fhP2L","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t{\n2\t  \"strategy\": \"Bottom-Up\",\n3\t  \"overview\": \"The leave-service has no dependencies and forms the foundation of the system, so it is built first. The leave-portal depends on leave-service for all API calls and cannot be meaningfully developed or tested without it, so it follows in Phase 2. This bottom-up ordering ensures each layer is ready before the layer above it is assembled.\",\n4\t  \"phases\": [\n5\t    {\n6\t      \"phase\": 1,\n7\t      \"name\": \"Foundation Services\",\n8\t      \"description\": \"The leave-service is the sole backend and has no dependencies on other components. It must be implemented first as it owns all business logic, data storage, and API contracts that the frontend will consume.\",\n9\t      \"components\": [\n10\t        {\n11\t          \"name\": \"leave-service\",\n12\t          \"componentType\": \"service\",\n13\t          \"language\": \"Go\",\n14\t          \"deployment\": \"Docker\",\n15\t          \"responsibilities\": [\n16\t            \"Handle submission, retrieval, and status updates of employee leave requests\",\n17\t            \"Enforce business rules including date-range validation, overlap detection, and balance sufficiency checks\",\n18\t            \"Manage leave balances per employee and deduct approved leave from the appropriate balance\",\n19\t            \"Support role-based filtering of leave requests for employees, managers, and HR admins\",\n20\t            \"Expose a /health endpoint for Kubernetes readiness probes\"\n21\t          ],\n22\t          \"architectureContext\": \"This is the sole backend service in the system. It is called directly by the leave-portal for all data operations. It stores all state in-memory (maps with mutexes) and seeds initial employee, manager, and balance data at startup. Nothing depends on an external service — it is the system's source of truth.\",\n23\t          \"keyConsiderations\": [\n24\t            \"In-memory store must use sync.RWMutex correctly to avoid data races under concurrent requests — use read locks for GET operations and write locks for POST/PATCH/PUT.\",\n25\t            \"Balance deduction must only occur when a request transitions to 'approved' via PATCH, not at submission time; guard against double-deduction if PATCH is called more than once.\",\n26\t            \"Overlap detection must check all existing non-denied requests for the same employeeId where date ranges intersect before creating a new request.\",\n27\t            \"Manager authorization in PATCH must verify that the reviewerId is registered as the direct manager of the leave request's employeeId — return 403 otherwise.\",\n28\t            \"Multi-stage Dockerfile must produce a minimal scratch-based final image; ensure the bina{"type":"system","subtype":"task_updated","task_id":"buovx91tg","patch":{"status":"killed","end_time":1776951128920},"uuid":"45f148df-6fa9-47a9-94c2-8955f7ca7063","session_id":"8874ace2-bdc7-4548-9b9e-797cc566d3d3"}
