{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SumBnGJdMrxaa1bwmn9L2p","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Based on my search, the local-dispatcher doesn't directly map GitHub issue numbers to task UUIDs. The dispatcher accepts taskId as a string in its DispatchRequest. The mapping likely happens at a higher level (the ASDLC platform). Let me check if there's any documentation or API call patterns:\n\n**Finding:** The ASDLC local-dispatcher does not directly handle GitHub issue-to-UUID mappings. The taskId is passed opaquely as a string parameter in dispatch requests. The mapping between GitHub issue #9 and its ASDLC task UUID would need to be:\n\n1. Stored in the ASDLC platform's database (accessible via the HTTP MCP endpoint at `http://localhost:9090/mcp/`)\n2. Managed by the platform, not the dispatcher\n\nThe dispatcher's type contract shows it simply tracks `taskId` (string) but doesn't parse or convert issue numbers. To find the exact UUID for issue #9, you would need to query the ASDLC platform's database directly or check your GitHub repository's ASDLC integration settings, which typically store issue-to-task mappings in the repo's `.asdlc` metadata."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4f4371ae-b5cb-4282-90f7-3ba15cbb2514","uuid":"b8f40b3b-d882-40cc-97c4-afa8d61ee497","timestamp":"2026-04-23T13:32:00.323Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Search for the ASDLC task UUID for GitHub issue #9. The ASDLC local dispatcher is at /Users/wso2/repos/asdlc/local-dispatcher. I need to find how it maps GitHub issue numbers to ASDLC UUID task IDs. Look for:\n1. Config files at /Users/wso2/.asdlc/ (recursively)\n2. Source files in /Users/wso2/repos/{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MgXfiBUe2tSpeArYi7Fyi5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems the Docker build is downloading a different image now (golang:1.23-alpine 