{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01V8ZnWsTQAVSdrYSqDjC5xJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Uask7R1Uak6Gmz5d2HxQEj","name":"mcp__asdlc__submit_implementation","input":{"taskId":"f36fff8c-7f79-4c3e-a8d3-7a31dfb2ed33","summary":"Implemented the complete leave-service Go HTTP backend on port 9090 with all endpoints from the OpenAPI spec:\n\n- GET /health → {\"status\":\"ok\"} with HTTP 200 (Kubernetes readiness probe)\n- POST /api/v1/leave-requests — creates leave request with date validation, overlap detection, and balance sufficiency check\n- GET /api/v1/leave-requests — lists requests filterable by employeeId, managerId, status\n- GET /api/v1/leave-requests/{id} — returns a specific request (404 if not found)\n- PATCH /api/v1/leave-requests/{id} — approves/denies with manager auth check (403 if wrong reviewer), deducts balance only on first approval transition\n- GET /api/v1/employees/{id}/balance — returns per-type allocations/used/remaining\n- PUT /api/v1/employees/{id}/balance — sets leave allocation for HR admin\n\nIn-memory store seeded with 3 employees (emp1, emp2, emp3) managed by mgr1; balances: 20 annual, 10 sick, 5 personal days each. Thread-safe using sync.RWMutex. Multi-stage Dockerfile (golang:1.21-alpine builder → scratch final image). workload.yaml configured for port 9090 with HTTP external endpoint.","port":9090,"filesCreated":["main.go","go.mod","Dockerfile","workload.yaml","internal/models/models.go","internal/handlers/handlers.go","internal/store/store.go"]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":331,"cache_read_input_tokens":86708,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":331,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"043e1b9a-cefb-